<item>
            <title>[SOLR-6992] ShowFileRequestHandler is hiding dynamic schema file even in read-only mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6992</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using dynamic schema, the schema file is not shown in the admin UI (Files tab) by default. It is hidden because (as per &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/blob/db33df44c037e04fea9ac3e391ef79c0d6ae04f4/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/handler/admin/ShowFileRequestHandler.java#L279&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;the section comment&lt;/a&gt;):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt; // Make sure that if the schema is managed, we don&apos;t allow editing. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But we don&apos;t have editing interface for those files (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5287&quot; title=&quot;Allow at least solrconfig.xml and schema.xml to be edited via the admin screen&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5287&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-5287&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was backed out), so the reason is not valid and makes reviewing schema just that bit harder.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is probably just editing out that section, unless there are tests specifically for that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
